Reasoning: The paper deals with cooperative wireless systems and their performance analysis in terms of diversity-multiplexing tradeoff. This topic falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science, including information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), systems and control (cs.SY), multimedia (cs.MM), and cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper specifically focuses on relay channels, multiple-access relay channels, and virtual MIMO systems, which are all relevant to these sub-categories.
